        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 8 at 2:53PM EDT by NWS Indianapolis IN</headline>
        <description>At 253 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from 12 miles northwest of Spencer to 8 miles west
of Martinsville to 7 miles north of Nashville. These storms were
nearly stationary.

HAZARD...Pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Martinsville, Nashville, Morgantown, Gosport, Paragon, Peoga,
Mahalasville, Quincy, Helmsburg, Beanblossom, Gnaw Bone,
Patricksburg, Spearsville, Devore, and Lake Lemon.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with these storms and may lead
to localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
